  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Big-Theta Notation Interactive Explorer</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>Big-Theta Notation Interactive Explorer</h1>\n\n<section id=\"definition-section\">\n  <h2>1. Definition and Overview</h2>\n  <p>\n    &Theta;(g(n)) = { f(n) | there exist positive constants c1, c2, n0 such that for all n ≥ n0,\n    c1 × g(n) ≤ f(n) ≤ c2 × g(n) }<br/>\n    Big-Theta notation describes a tight bound on the growth rate of functions.\n  </p>\n  <button id=\"show-formal-def\">Show Formal Definition</button>\n  <div id=\"formal-definition\" style=\"display:none; white-space: pre-wrap; border: 1px solid black; padding: 5px; margin-top:5px; max-width:600px;\">\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<section id=\"function-builder-section\">\n  <h2>2. Build & Compare Functions</h2>\n  <p>\n    Create functions f(n) and g(n) using predefined terms and test if f(n) = &Theta;(g(n)).\n  </p>\n\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"fterms\">Select terms for f(n):</label><br/>\n    <select id=\"fterms\" multiple size=\"6\" aria-label=\"Function f(n) terms\">\n      <option value=\"1\">1 (constant)</option>\n      <option value=\"log\">log n (logarithmic)</option>\n      <option value=\"n\">n (linear)</option>\n      <option value=\"nlog\">n log n</option>\n      <option value=\"n2\">n² (quadratic)</option>\n      <option value=\"exp\">2^n (exponential)</option>\n    </select>\n  </div>\n\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"fcoeff\">Coefficients for f(n) terms (comma separated):</label><br/>\n    <input id=\"fcoeff\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"e.g. 3,0,1,0,2,0\" aria-label=\"Coefficients for f(n)\" size=\"50\"/>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <label for=\"gterms\">Select terms for g(n):</label><br/>\n    <select id=\"gterms\" multiple size=\"6\" aria-label=\"Function g(n) terms\">\n      <option value=\"1\">1 (constant)</option>\n      <option value=\"log\">log n (logarithmic)</option>\n      <option value=\"n\">n (linear)</option>\n      <option value=\"nlog\">n log n</option>\n      <option value=\"n2\">n² (quadratic)</option>\n      <option value=\"exp\">2^n (exponential)</option>\n    </select>\n  </div>\n\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"gcoeff\">Coefficients for g(n) terms (comma separated):</label><br/>\n    <input id=\"gcoeff\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"e.g. 1,0,1,0,0,0\" aria-label=\"Coefficients for g(n)\" size=\"50\"/>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <label for=\"nstart\">Start n (≥ 1): </label>\n    <input id=\"nstart\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" value=\"1\" aria-label=\"Start n\"/>\n    \n    <label for=\"nend\" style=\"margin-left:10px;\">End n (≥ Start n): </label>\n    <input id=\"nend\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" value=\"100\" aria-label=\"End n\"/>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <button id=\"evaluate-btn\">Evaluate f(n) versus Θ(g(n))</button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"evaluation-result\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top:10px; border: 1px solid black; padding: 5px; max-width:650px; min-height:60px;\"></div>\n</section>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<section id=\"explorer-section\">\n  <h2>3. Step-by-Step Exploration</h2>\n  <p>\n    Explore the constants c1, c2 and n0 used to establish Θ-bound.<br/>\n    Adjust constants and see bounds and inequalities for chosen n values.\n  </p>\n\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"const-c1\">c<sub>1</sub> (lower bound constant): </label>\n    <input id=\"const-c1\" type=\"number\" step=\"0.01\" min=\"0\" value=\"0.5\" aria-label=\"c1 constant\"/>\n  </div>\n\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"const-c2\">c<sub>2</sub> (upper bound constant): </label>\n    <input id=\"const-c2\" type=\"number\" step=\"0.01\" min=\"0\" value=\"2\" aria-label=\"c2 constant\"/>\n  </div>\n\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"const-n0\">n<sub>0</sub> (starting n): </label>\n    <input id=\"const-n0\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" value=\"10\" aria-label=\"n0 constant\"/>\n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"margin-top:10px;\">\n    <button id=\"update-bounds-btn\">Update Bound Check</button>\n  </div>\n\n  <div id=\"bounds-check-result\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top:10px; border: 1px solid black; padding: 5px; max-width:650px; min-height:120px;\">\n  </div>\n</section>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<section id=\"function-evaluator\">\n  <h2>4. Evaluate Functions at Specific n</h2>\n  <p>Test computed values of f(n) and g(n) at chosen n.</p>\n  <div>\n    <label for=\"eval-n\">n = </label>\n    <input id=\"eval-n\" type=\"number\" min=\"1\" step=\"1\" value=\"20\" aria-label=\"Evaluate at n\"/>\n    <button id=\"eval-btn\">Evaluate</button>\n  </div>\n  <div id=\"eval-result\" style=\"white-space: pre-wrap; margin-top:10px; border: 1px solid black; padding: 5px; max-width:650px; min-height:40px;\"></div>\n</section>\n\n<hr/>\n\n<section id=\"help-section\">\n  <h2>Help / Instructions</h2>\n  <p>\n    <strong>How to use this tool:</strong><br/>\n    1. Select terms and enter coefficients for f(n) and g(n). The order of coefficients corresponds to the order of terms shown.<br/>\n    2. Specify the range of n values over which to test f(n) ≤ c2·g(n) and f(n) ≥ c1·g(n).<br/>\n    3. Click \"Evaluate f(n) versus Θ(g(n))\" to determine whether f(n) = Θ(g(n)) seems plausible within tested range.<br/>\n    4. Then explore constants c1, c2, and n0 explicitly to see inequalities detailed.<br/>\n    5. Use Evaluate Functions at Specific n to check numeric values.<br/>\n    <br/>\n    <strong>Notes:</strong><br/>\n    - Multiple terms are summed to create the functions.<br/>\n    - If g(n) becomes zero or negative in range, results may be invalid.<br/>\n    - The tool uses sampled n values and simple numerical checks.<br/>\n  </p>\n</section>\n\n<script>\n(function(){\n  const termsList = ['1','log','n','nlog','n2','exp'];\n  // term evaluators: input n => value\n  const funcs = {\n    '1': n => 1,\n    'log': n => (n>1 ? Math.log2(n) : 0),\n    'n': n => n,\n    'nlog': n => n * (n>1 ? Math.log2(n) : 0),\n    'n2': n => n*n,\n    'exp': n => Math.pow(2,n)\n  };\n\n  // Show formal definition button\n  const showFormalBtn = document.getElementById('show-formal-def');\n  const formalDiv = document.getElementById('formal-definition');\n  showFormalBtn.onclick = () => {\n    if(formalDiv.style.display === 'none'){\n      formalDiv.textContent =\n`Big-Theta notation: Θ(g(n)) = { f(n) :\n\nThere exist positive constants c1, c2, and n0 such that ∀ n ≥ n0:\n\nc1 × g(n) ≤ f(n) ≤ c2 × g(n) }`;\n      formalDiv.style.display = 'block';\n      showFormalBtn.textContent = 'Hide Formal Definition';\n    } else {\n      formalDiv.style.display = 'none';\n      showFormalBtn.textContent = 'Show Formal Definition';\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Utility: parse coefficients lists for f or g\n  function parseCoeffs(input){\n    // Split by comma\n    let parts = input.split(',').map(s=>s.trim()).filter(s=>s.length>0);\n    if(parts.length === 0) return null;\n    // Convert to numbers, return null on invalid\n    let nums = parts.map(x=>Number(x));\n    if(nums.some(x=> isNaN(x))) return null;\n    return nums;\n  }\n\n  // Build function evaluator from selected terms and coefficients\n  // Return a function n => sum of selected terms * coefficients\n  // termsSelection: array of term strings (note: order matters), coeffs: numeric array for these terms in order of termsList\n  // We have multiple selected terms - we must map each term to its coefficient at correct index\n  // Terms in select can be multi (multiple options selected, order is selection order? but select multiple: options order, treat selected options in order they appear? We'll respect the full list order but set 0 coeff if term not selected\n  function buildFuncFromSelection(selectedOpts, coeffsArr){\n    // Map each term to its coefficient or zero\n    // selectedOpts is a list of strings (terms from termsList)\n    // coeffsArr must have length at least termsList.length, we map termsList index to coeff\n    // We'll create an index-guided approach where terms in termsList correspond to coefficients\n    // For missing selections (terms not selected but coeff given?), ignore coeff, but we accept coeffs for all terms\n    // So we build function sum over all terms of coeff * func(term)\n    if(coeffsArr.length < termsList.length) return null;\n    // Construct f(n)\n    return function(n){\n      let sum = 0;\n      for(let i=0;i<termsList.length;i++){\n        if(selectedOpts.includes(termsList[i])){\n          let c = coeffsArr[i];\n          if(typeof c !== 'number' || isNaN(c)) return NaN;\n          let v = funcs[termsList[i]](n);\n          // If v is NaN or Infinite, treat as NaN (defensive)\n          if(!isFinite(v)) return NaN;\n          sum += c*v;\n        }\n      }\n      return sum;\n    };\n  }\n\n  // Button: Evaluate f(n) vs Theta(g(n))\n  const evaluateBtn = document.getElementById('evaluate-btn');\n  const evalResultDiv = document.getElementById('evaluation-result');\n\n  evaluateBtn.onclick = () => {\n    evalResultDiv.textContent = '';\n    // Read selections & inputs\n    const fselect = Array.from(document.getElementById('fterms').selectedOptions).map(o=>o.value);\n    const gselect = Array.from(document.getElementById('gterms').selectedOptions).map(o=>o.value);\n    const fcoeffStr = document.getElementById('fcoeff').value;\n    const gcoeffStr = document.getElementById('gcoeff').value;\n    const nstart = Number(document.getElementById('nstart').value);\n    const nend = Number(document.getElementById('nend').value);\n\n    if(fselect.length === 0){\n      evalResultDiv.textContent = 'Please select at least one term for f(n).';\n      return;\n    }\n    if(gselect.length === 0){\n      evalResultDiv.textContent = 'Please select at least one term for g(n).';\n      return;\n    }\n    if(isNaN(nstart) || isNaN(nend) || nstart < 1 || nend < nstart){\n      evalResultDiv.textContent = 'Please enter valid n range (start ≥1 and end ≥ start).';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    const fcoeffs = parseCoeffs(fcoeffStr);\n    const gcoeffs = parseCoeffs(gcoeffStr);\n    if(fcoeffs === null || fcoeffs.length < termsList.length){\n      evalResultDiv.textContent = 'Invalid coefficients for f(n). Must include at least ' + termsList.length + ' comma-separated numbers.';\n      return;\n    }\n    if(gcoeffs === null || gcoeffs.length < termsList.length){\n      evalResultDiv.textContent = 'Invalid coefficients for g(n). Must include at least ' + termsList.length + ' comma-separated numbers.';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Build f and g functions\n    const f_func = buildFuncFromSelection(fselect, fcoeffs);\n    const g_func = buildFuncFromSelection(gselect, gcoeffs);\n    if(f_func === null || g_func === null){\n      evalResultDiv.textContent = 'Error building functions from inputs.';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Check values for all n from nstart to nend (sampled for performance)\n    // To avoid too many points, sample at up to 100 points with integer steps (or less)\n\n    let step = 1;\n    if(nend-nstart > 100) step = Math.floor((nend-nstart)/100);\n\n    // We want to find constants c1, c2, and n0 such that for all n≥n0,\n    // c1*g(n) ≤ f(n) ≤ c2*g(n)\n    // We'll scan possible n0 in [nstart..nend], and compute for n≥n0:\n    // c1 <= min over all n≥n0 of f(n)/g(n)\n    // c2 >= max over all n≥n0 of f(n)/g(n)\n    // If g(n) == 0 or negative, skip that point or invalidate?\n\n    // collect ratios f(n)/g(n)\n    // We must handle case g(n) close to zero or negative (skip or treat as invalid)\n\n    let ratiosByN = [];\n    for(let n = nstart; n <= nend; n+= step){\n      let fn = f_func(n);\n      let gn = g_func(n);\n      if(!isFinite(fn) || !isFinite(gn)) continue;\n      if(gn <= 0) continue; // skip non-positive g(n) values because ratio undefined or negative invalid\n      ratiosByN.push({n:n, ratio: fn/gn});\n    }\n    if(ratiosByN.length === 0){\n      evalResultDiv.textContent = 'No valid data points for analysis (g(n) non-positive or undefined).';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Try all n0 candidates from nstart to nend - this is a key user-explorable step!\n    // We'll pick the \"best\" n0 giving the tightest (non-empty) c1, c2 with c1 ≤ c2\n    // For each n0 candidate, consider only ratios for n≥n0:\n    // Compute c1 = min ratio, c2 = max ratio\n    // If c1 ≤ c2 and both positive, record it.\n\n    const n0_candidates = [];\n    for(let candidate = nstart; candidate <= nend; candidate += step){\n      const filteredRatios = ratiosByN.filter(pt => pt.n >= candidate);\n      if(filteredRatios.length === 0) continue;\n      const c1 = Math.min(...filteredRatios.map(pt=>pt.ratio));\n      const c2 = Math.max(...filteredRatios.map(pt=>pt.ratio));\n      if(c1 > c2) continue; // nonsense\n      if(c2 < 0) continue; // all negative - ignore\n      n0_candidates.push({\n        n0: candidate,\n        c1: c1,\n        c2: c2,\n        rangeLength: filteredRatios.length\n      });\n    }\n    if(n0_candidates.length === 0){\n      evalResultDiv.textContent = 'No suitable n0 found with positive bounding constants c1 and c2.';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    // Sort candidates by (c2 - c1) ascending, then n0 ascending\n    n0_candidates.sort((a,b) => {\n      let diffA = a.c2 - a.c1;\n      let diffB = b.c2 - b.c1;\n      if(diffA !== diffB) return diffA - diffB;\n      return a.n0 - b.n0;\n    });\n\n\n    // Pick best candidate (tightest bounds)\n    const best = n0_candidates[0];\n    // Build summary:\n    let text = '';\n    text += 'Evaluation for f(n) and Θ(g(n)) from n = ' + nstart + ' to ' + nend + ' (step approx ' + step + ')\\n\\n';\n    text += 'Selected n0: ' + best.n0 + '\\n';\n    text += 'Bounds found:\\n';\n    text += '  c1 (lower bound) = ' + best.c1.toFixed(4) + '\\n';\n    text += '  c2 (upper bound) = ' + best.c2.toFixed(4) + '\\n';\n    text += '\\nInterpretation:\\n';\n    if(best.c1 > 0 && best.c2 < Infinity && best.c1 <= best.c2){\n      text += 'f(n) appears to be Θ(g(n)) for n ≥ ' + best.n0 + ' using these bounds.\\n';\n      text += 'Meaning: for n ≥ ' + best.n0 + ', c1·g(n) ≤ f(n) ≤ c2·g(n) approximately holds.\\n';\n      text += '(Note: numerical approximation and sampling applied.)\\n';\n    } else {\n      text += 'Could not confirm f(n) = Θ(g(n)) with these data.\\n';\n    }\n    text += '\\nYou may adjust constants in section 3 to explore further.';\n    evalResultDiv.textContent = text;\n\n    // Store f_func, g_func and best parameters globally for other sections:\n    window._fFunc = f_func;\n    window._gFunc = g_func;\n    window._currentBounds = {c1:best.c1, c2:best.c2, n0:best.n0};\n    window._currentRange = {nstart:nstart, nend:nend, step:step};\n  };\n\n\n  // Section 3: Bounds check on constants c1, c2, n0\n  const updateBoundsBtn = document.getElementById('update-bounds-btn');\n  const boundsCheckDiv = document.getElementById('bounds-check-result');\n\n  updateBoundsBtn.onclick = () => {\n    boundsCheckDiv.textContent = '';\n\n    if(!window._fFunc || !window._gFunc){\n      boundsCheckDiv.textContent = 'Error: Please evaluate f(n) vs Θ(g(n)) in section 2 first.';\n      return;\n    }\n\n    let c1 = Number(document.getElementById('const-c1').value);\n    let c2 = Number(document.getElementById('const-c2').value);\n    let n0 = Number(document.getElementById('const-n0').value);\n\n    if(isNaN(c1) || isNaN(c2) || isNaN(n0) || c1 < 0 || c2 < 0 || n0 < 1){\n      boundsCheckDiv.textContent = 'Please enter valid non-negative c1, c2 and n0 ≥ 1.';\n      return;\n    }\n    if(c2 < c1){\n      boundsCheckDiv.textContent = 'Warning: c2 should be ≥ c1 to form a valid bound.';\n    }\n\n    const f_func = window._fFunc;\n    const g_func = window._gFunc;\n\n    // Sample values n0, n0+step, ..., up to current nend or n0+1000 max points\n    const nstart = n0;\n    const maxSamples = 1000;\n    const step = 1;\n    let currentMaxN = window._currentRange? window._currentRange.nend : n0+maxSamples;\n\n    const nend = Math.min(currentMaxN, n0+maxSamples);\n\n    // Check for each n≥n0:\n    // Does c1*g(n) ≤ f(n) ≤ c2*g(n) hold?\n\n    // Gather violations:\n    let violations = [];\n    for(let n = nstart; n <= nend; n += step){\n      let fn = f_func(n);\n      let gn = g_func(n);\n      if(!isFinite(fn) || !isFinite(gn)) continue; // skip invalid\n      let lower = c1 * gn;\n      let upper = c2 * gn;\n      if(gn < 0){\n        // Inequality less meaningful if g(n)<0, mark as warning but skip check\n        violations.push({n:n, type:'g(n)<0', f:fn, g:gn});\n        continue;\n      }\n      if(fn < lower || fn > upper){\n        violations.push({n:n, type:'violation', f:fn, g:gn, lower:lower, upper:upper});\n      }\n    }\n\n    if(violations.length === 0){\n      boundsCheckDiv.textContent = `All tested n from n = ${nstart} to n = ${nend} satisfy:\\n  c1·g(n) ≤ f(n) ≤ c2·g(n)\\n\\nConstants chosen seem valid bounds for this range.`;\n    } else {\n      let text = '';\n      text += `Found ${violations.length} violations or warnings for n from ${nstart} to ${nend}:\\n\\n`;\n      let warnCount = 0;\n      let violationCount = 0;\n      for(let i=0; i<violations.length && i< 20; i++){\n        let v = violations[i];\n        if(v.type === 'g(n)<0'){\n          warnCount++;\n          text += `n=${v.n}: g(n) = ${v.g.toFixed(4)} < 0, skipping inequality check.\\n`;\n        } else {\n          violationCount++;\n          text += `n=${v.n}: f(n) = ${v.f.toFixed(4)} NOT in [${v.lower.toFixed(4)}, ${v.upper.toFixed(4)}]\\n`;\n        }\n      }\n      if(violations.length > 20){\n        text += `... and ${violations.length - 20} more.\\n`;\n      }\n      if(warnCount > 0){\n        text += `\\nNote: Some values of g(n) < 0 - inequalities less meaningful there.\\n`;\n      }\n      if(violationCount > 0){\n        text += `\\nConclusion: Constants c1 and c2 do NOT bound f(n) tightly from below and above respectively for all tested n.\\n`;\n      }\n      boundsCheckDiv.textContent = text;\n    }\n  };\n\n  // Section 4: Evaluate functions at specific n\n  const evalNInput = document.getElementById('eval-n');\n  const evalBtn = document.getElementById('eval-btn');\n  const evalResultDiv = document.getElementById('eval-result');\n\n  evalBtn.onclick = () => {\n    evalResultDiv.textContent = '';\n    if(!window._fFunc || !window._gFunc){\n      evalResultDiv.textContent = 'Error: Please evaluate functions in section 2 first.';\n      return;\n    }\n    let n = Number(evalNInput.value);\n    if(isNaN(n) || n < 1){\n      evalResultDiv.textContent = 'Please enter valid n (≥ 1).';\n      return;\n    }\n    let fval = window._fFunc(n);\n    let gval = window._gFunc(n);\n\n    if(!isFinite(fval) || !isFinite(gval)){\n      evalResultDiv.textContent = 'Function returned invalid values at n=' + n;\n      return;\n    }\n\n    evalResultDiv.textContent = 'At n = ' + n + ':\\n' +\n      'f(n) = ' + fval.toFixed(6) + '\\n' +\n      'g(n) = ' + gval.toFixed(6) + '\\n' +\n      (gval !== 0 ? 'f(n)/g(n) = ' + (fval/gval).toFixed(6) : 'g(n) = 0, cannot compute ratio.');\n  };\n\n  // Initialization: set default coeff values that match default terms selected on each list (none selected by default)\n  // We select basic defaults to help users:\n  const ftermsSelect = document.getElementById('fterms');\n  const gtermsSelect = document.getElementById('gterms');\n  // Select a basic default: f: n2 and n selected, g: n2 selected (example)\n  ftermsSelect.selectedIndex = -1;\n  gtermsSelect.selectedIndex = -1;\n\n  // Example preset: f(n) = 3*n^2 + 0 * others\n  // Insert default coefficients string with zeroes for all but quadratic (index 4) -> 3\n  document.getElementById('fcoeff').value = \"0,0,0,0,3,0\";\n  // g(n) = 1*n^2 default\n  document.getElementById('gcoeff').value = \"0,0,0,0,1,0\";\n\n  // Select corresponding terms for f and g by default for ease of demo:\n  // Helper to select given values in select multiple\n  function selectValues(selectElem, values){\n    for(let o of selectElem.options){\n      o.selected = values.includes(o.value);\n    }\n  }\n  selectValues(ftermsSelect, ['n2']);\n  selectValues(gtermsSelect, ['n2']);\n})();\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
